HEADWORD: Wootz
<hw>Wootz</hw> <pr>(w⟦oomac⟧ts)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Perhaps a
corruption of Canarese <ets>ukku</ets> steel.]</ety> <def>A species of
steel imported from the East Indies, valued for making edge tools;
Indian steel. It has in combination a minute portion of alumina and
silica.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

